    <text id="B0071T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Helfelfinger writes that a boy in his employ ran away without giving notice and
                    broke his contract. An attached note gives the boy's full name as Jesse
                Lewis.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Thos P. Jackson <unclear>Esq</unclear><lb/>Staunton</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-02-02"><abbr expan="February">Feb</abbr> 2<hi rend="super">d</hi> 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Augusta Alum</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute><abbr expan="Dear">Dr</abbr> Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Your favor of Jan 29<hi rend="super">th</hi> is <abbr expan="received"
                    >recd</abbr>. The boy Jesse commenced work for me on the 8<hi rend="super"
                    >th</hi> of <abbr expan="October">Oct</abbr> last, having agreed to work by the
                        <hi rend="underline">month</hi> from that date @ $8.00 per <abbr
                        expan="month">mon</abbr>; Sometime before his month was out he ran away
                    without giving me any notice or leaving me with anyone to supply his place thus
                    breaking his contract &amp; depriving himself of all claim on me. I was away
                    during the most of his stay here &amp; my clerk informs me that he was
                    utterly worthless &amp; did not earn his board</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully</salute>
                    <signed>J.A. Hefelfinger</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
